# GitHub API Configuration
# =========================
# 
# DEVELOPMENT NOTES:
# - GitHub API has rate limits: 60 requests/hour for unauthenticated requests
# - With a personal access token: 5,000 requests/hour
# - For production use, you MUST add a GitHub token to avoid rate limiting
#
# HOW TO GET A GITHUB TOKEN:
# 1. Go to https://github.com/settings/tokens
# 2. Click "Generate new token" -> "Generate new token (classic)"
# 3. Add note: "Canonical Contribution Tracker"
# 4. Select scopes: 
#    -  public_repo (access public repositories)
#    -  read:org (read organization data) 
# 5. Click "Generate token"
# 6. Copy the token and paste it below
#
# SETUP:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local
# 2. Replace 'your_github_token_here' with your actual token
# 3. Restart your development server

VITE_GITHUB_TOKEN=your_github_token_here
